---
// creating-an-astro-static-site.astro
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Creating an Astro Static Site | Cosmic Astro">
  <article class="blog-post">
    <h1>Creating an Astro Static Site</h1>
    <p>Astro is a modern static site generator that helps you build lightning-fast websites with minimal JavaScript. In this post, I share how I set up my project, created reusable components, and embraced Astro's efficient rendering.</p>
    <p>Getting started is easy: run <code>npm create astro@latest</code>, choose a template, install dependencies, and build your site. Astro's component model lets you quickly assemble pages with consistent design.</p>
    <p>This approach speeds up development and yields a highly optimized site that loads quickly even on low-powered devices.</p>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .blog-post {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 2rem auto;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    border-radius: 8px;
    color: var(--text-color);
  }
  .blog-post h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .blog-post p {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  code {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
    padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
</style>
